Investigations are ongoing after a woman was allegedly been raped and stabbed in Alberton, on the East Rand, on Tuesday. It is alleged a man broke into a house on Humphreys Street before raping and stabbing the woman and fled into the veld, Alberton Record reported. According to Elowayne Gouws, from Fox Security s medical unit, they were awaiting backup to search for the suspect. It is not yet known how serious the victim s wounds are, but Gouws says the stabbing was not fatal. This follows a spate of serious crime plaguing Alberton recently. &#8211; Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter .